    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in **Jackson Merrill**, whose 75.10 projection makes him our strongest start. Facing Ryan Feltner, **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a massive 14% park boost and a favorable matchup against a 4.63 xERA arm; his 3-hole positioning significantly elevates his efficiency, making him the anchor of our lineup. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** is our next most reliable option at 71.33. He draws a high-leverage opportunity in the 2-hole against Ritchie, where his dynamic platoon advantage provides a 14% boost, effectively negating the moderate difficulty of the opposing pitcher. **Drake Baldwin** also warrants attention as a strong play (61.45), as his prime placement in the 2-hole against Cavalli provides a steady floor for our C1 spot.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Josh Jung**, whose 41.26 score kept him squarely in the \"marginal\" territory. Ultimately, the optimizer prioritized the higher ceiling of our outfield depth against weaker pitchers, despite the risk associated with pending lineups. We must remain cautious with our star-studded outfield trio of **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Andy Pages**, and **Heliot Ramos**. While they are active, they face significant headwinds today against elite arms like Joe Ryan, Logan Webb, and Tyler Glasnow. Specifically, **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Andy Pages** are saddled with high-skill SP penalties exceeding 16%, limiting their upside. Additionally, **Marcell Ozuna** faces a formidable test against Jacob deGrom; his score of 44.24 is dampened by a poor BvP history and the general danger of the matchup. With **Jordan Westburg** sidelined on the IL, we are closely monitoring the status of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Gunnar Henderson**, both of whom are unavailable today due to team off-days, forcing us to lean heavily on the performance of **Kyle Tucker** and the rest of our active squad to navigate these tough pitching assignments.",
